113 g Corn Kernels
2 unit(s) Cream Cheese
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
7 g Chives
2 unit(s) Flatbread
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Peel, then mince garlic. Cut each flatbread into 6 wedges (12 wedges total). Stir together half the garlic and 1 tbsp oil in a small bowl. Arrange flatbread wedges on a foil-lined baking sheet. Brush tops with garlic oil. Season with salt and pepper. Broil in the middle of the oven until flatbread wedges are golden-brown, 2-3 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on wedges so they don't burn!)

While flatbread wedges broil, pat corn dry with paper towels. Thinly slice chives. Stir together cream cheese, corn, sour cream, half the chives, remaining garlic, half the mozzarella, 1/4 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper in a baking dish until combined. Spread into an even layer.

Sprinkle remaining mozzarella over dip. Broil dip in the middle of the oven until warmed through, 2-3 min.

Sprinkle remaining chives over dip. Serve garlic flatbread chips on the side for dipping.